  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Appeal for Humanitarian Response in Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Distribution of standard food package to 410 people. Each food pack will support family of 5 people, on an average, for 30 days.     
- Distribution of special food package with nutrition components to 170 pregnant and lactating women 
- Distribution of hygiene dignity kits to 410 women and girls 
- Conducting life skill trainings to 1200 women and girls 
Raising awareness on GBV and SGBV to 2000 individuals</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- The proposed initiative is going to provide assistance to IDPs, returnees and the most poor and marginalized papulation among host community, settled in center of Herat city, Herat province. 
- People were displaced because of ongoing clashes and natural disasters. Currently the board target areas have been identified based on CSO assessments under the leadership of OCHA, Heart, to  Increased food security and promotion of life skills education among women and girls in the majority of IDP settlement areas in Herat province</narrative>
  </description>
